            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", the search controller coordinates with a search results controller to display the search results."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "On iOS, incorporate the search controllerâ€™s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uisearchcontroller/1618657-searchbar"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " into your own view controllerâ€™s interface. Display your view controller in whatever way is appropriate for your app. See "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/view_controllers/displaying_searchable_content_by_using_a_search_controller"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/view_controllers/using_suggested_searches_with_a_search_controller"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to learn how to implement a search controller in your app."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "On tvOS, start with a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uisearchcontainerviewcontroller"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to manage the presentation of the search controller. See "
            },
            {
              "type": "link",
              "title": "UIKit Catalog (tvOS): Creating and Customizing UIKit Controls",
              "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/samplecode/UICatalogFortvOS/Introduction/Intro.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40016433"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to learn how to implement a search controller embedded inside a "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "UISearchContainerViewController"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Donâ€™t use a "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uisearchcontainerviewcontroller"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " on iOS."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "note",
          "name": "Note"
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Display Search Results",
          "anchor": "3678710"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Specify a second view controller for displaying search results when you call "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uisearchcontroller/1618647-initwithsearchresultscontroller"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". When the user interacts with the search bar, the search controller automatically displays the results controller with the results you specify. If your results view is full screen on tvOS, set the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uisearchcontroller/3584820-searchcontrollerobservedscrollvi"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to the results controller as well, so the search bar scrolls with your content view. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Provide a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uisearchresultsupdating"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object to the search controllerâ€™s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uisearchcontroller/1618661-searchresultsupdater"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property. Typically, the view controller with your searchable content also acts as the search results updater object, but you can use another object if you prefer. When the user interacts with the search bar, the search controller calls the appropriate "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uisearchresultsupdating"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method, giving your object the opportunity to perform the search and update the contents of your search results view. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Customize Transitions",
          "anchor": "3678709"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To customize the presentation or dismissal of the search results controller, set the search controllerâ€™s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uisearchcontroller/1618654-delegate"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property to an object that conforms to the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uisearchcontrollerdelegate"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " protocol. Then implement delegate methods in this object to receive presentation and dismissal events from the search controller."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
